 provides access to the web services of a three tier infrastructures using ssl encryption with strong authentication these programs are cross platform self updating thick client applications that provides a rich user interface for data entry retrieval and review as well as image manipulation and annotation stride makes extensive use of xml technologies for representation of structured meta data distributed systems technologies using json for secure remote communication between client and server and swing graphical interface components providing a rich widget set as well as advanced imaging and graphing capabilities users of the stride research desktop client can perform rapid data entry into structured fields compose complex queries and interact securely with clinical research and imaging data read more view a presentation on stride read a paper describing the stride project view a video of a stride presentation at nih you are here current tab 4 stanford medicine school of medicine centers & programs scci research navigation for this section research overview stride text mining controlled clinical vocabularies similarity matching record linkage site navigation about the center about us mission people what is clinical informatics contact the center services overview access to clinical data research data managementment solutions real time research alerting biospecimen data management research privacy and security free consultation service collaborations overview spotlight sumc community anesthesia cancer center orthopedics pediatrics other departments research overview stride text mining clinical vocabularies similarity matching record linkage resources informatics resources citation information stanford medicine resources stanford medicine getting care overview find a physician find a clinical care center stanford hospital & clinics lucile packard children's hospital emergency research overview school of medicine news & resources clinical trials departments institute